<span id="freeTextContainer426834796639746978">Just saying, if the author&apos;s foreword includes spoilers to the solution of the mystery, it really oughta be an afterword.<br/><br/>Aside from that, about 2.5 stars. The mystery was of average complexity, the characters and storytelling style pretty melodramatic (I got an ironic chuckle out of the fact that <i>The Leavenworth Case</i> was mentioned and referred to as &quot;light&quot; reading, when I&apos;d rate <i>The Mystery of a Hansom Cab</i> rather lighter). Probably the most fun aspect was the setting of Victorian-era Australia,</span>
  <span id="freeText426834796639746978" style="display:none">Just saying, if the author's foreword includes spoilers to the solution of the mystery, it really oughta be an afterword.<br /><br />Aside from that, about 2.5 stars. The mystery was of average complexity, the characters and storytelling style pretty melodramatic (I got an ironic chuckle out of the fact that <i>The Leavenworth Case</i> was mentioned and referred to as "light" reading, when I'd rate <i>The Mystery of a Hansom Cab</i> rather lighter). Probably the most fun aspect was the setting of Victorian-era Australia, as I've read almost nothing else set there and the descriptions of the time and place were all fresh to me.</span>
