<div id="review_4018388408" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4018388408" />
    <a title="Erik Deckers" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/16238334-erik-deckers"><img alt="Erik Deckers" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1483820208p2/16238334.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4018388408?book_show_action=true">May 23, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Erik Deckers" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Erik Deckers" href="/user/show/16238334-erik-deckers">Erik Deckers</a>
      </span>

          added it


          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/9213480-the-mystery-of-a-hansom-cab">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4018388408" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6597212998208232409"><strong>Reads very slowly</strong><br/><br/>Ybis is an interesting look back at early detective fiction. It&apos;s inferesting to see where the genre came from, and it&apos;s a bit irritating to see so much misinformation and Victorian scientific beliefs, like brain fever. </span>
  <span id="freeText6597212998208232409" style="display:none"><strong>Reads very slowly</strong><br /><br />Ybis is an interesting look back at early detective fiction. It's inferesting to see where the genre came from, and it's a bit irritating to see so much misinformation and Victorian scientific beliefs, like brain fever. </span>
